# Radar Data Collection Guide

This guide explains how to collect radar data using the ORANGE SAR software and convert the recorded data into a Python-readable `.pkl` file for further processing.

## Prerequisites

* Git installed
* Python 3 installed
* SSH access to the radar computer
* Network connection to the PulsON 440 radar system

---

## 1. Clone the Repository

Clone the ORANGE SAR repository to your local machine.

```bash
git clone https://github.com/Csum99/ORANGE_SAR.git
```

---

## 2. Connect to the Radar Computer

SSH into the radar computer using its username and IP address.

```bash
ssh username@ip_address
```

---

## 3. Navigate to the Radar Software

```bash
cd ORANGE_SAR/pulson440
```

---

## 4. Install Required Python Packages

Install the required dependencies.

```bash
pip install -r pip_requirements.txt
```

> **Note:** This only needs to be done once for a new Python environment.

---

## 5. Start Data Collection

Begin collecting radar data.

```bash
python control.py --collect
```

The radar will continuously collect data until the process is stopped.

---

## 6. Stop Data Collection

Press **Ctrl + C** in the terminal to end the scan.

The collected data will be saved as a `.prd` file (for example, `collect_1.prd`).

---

## 7. Convert the Data

Convert the recorded `.prd` file into a Python pickle (`.pkl`) file for visualization and processing.

```bash
python unpack.py collect_#.prd collect_#.pkl -v
```

Replace `#` with the appropriate scan number.

**Example**

```bash
python unpack.py collect_1.prd collect_1.pkl -v
```

The `-v` flag displays information about the conversion process.
